    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02171.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="center">Kents Corner<ptr target="n0262"/></name>
                    <name type="place" rend="center">Well Road</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="center">Hampstead</name>
                    <date when="1880-12-13" rend="right">Dec 13th</date>
                    <date when="1880-12-13" rend="right">1880.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Walt</salute>       
            </opener>
            
            <p>Mother has been very ill;<ptr target="n0259"/> but is a little better now: &amp; with <choice><abbr>grt</abbr><expan>great</expan></choice> care will I hope be very much better. You will do me a kind service if you will receive this money order for payment of duty I <choice><orig>havent</orig><reg>haven't</reg></choice> the remotest idea how much it is &amp; if you will let me know the difference I will remit it. I should be glad if Mr<hi rend="underline">s</hi> Stafford<ptr target="n0817"/> could have the book by Xmas day.</p>
            
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Herbert H Gilchrist</signed>
            </closer>
